Jugaad Concept

The existing file upload portal has a poor user interface that makes the upload process confusing and inefficient. A simple redesign was created using basic UI/UX principles without changing the backend functionality. The improved interface organizes the layout, adds useful action buttons (Preview, Download, Delete Upload, Cancel Upload), displays multiple batches clearly, and provides better spacing. This is an example of frugal innovation (Jugaad), where a better user experience is achieved through thoughtful interface design rather than expensive software redevelopment.

Description

The original file upload page has a plain layout with poor alignment, limited options, and only a single batch visible at a time. Users cannot preview uploaded files, download them for verification, or cancel an accidental upload. The redesigned interface groups related components together, provides adequate spacing, supports multiple batch selections, and introduces additional controls such as Preview, Download, Delete Upload, and Cancel Upload. These improvements make the application more user-friendly, reduce user errors, and improve overall efficiency without modifying the core functionality of the system.

